Original recipe (1X) yields 10 servings Gather ingredients and preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). &lt;img alt="Ingredients for a casserole recipe including shredded cheese chicken black beans corn and various garnishes and seasonings arranged in bowls" class="img--noscript mntl-image mntl-image universal-image__image" height="3000" sizes="750px" src="img/d66b736148b138cf5711a7c66d8e58d8.webp" srcset="img/57298b95b71d87b7902ebf7796fa483e.webp 750w" width="4000"&gt; Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium. Add onion, jalepeño chile, and garlic, and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes. Add taco seasoning and cook, stirring often, until fragrant, about 1 minute. &lt;img alt="Cooking ingredients being stirred in a pan with a spatula" class="img--noscript mntl-image mntl-image universal-image__image" height="3000" sizes="750px" src="img/0bb5f1231895c451d2b5d2090038134a.webp" srcset="img/e2883e598f4f804f1085d8f4d615edc6.webp 750w" width="4000"&gt; Add salsa, bring to a simmer over medium, then add in cream cheese and salt, and cook, stirring constantly, until melted and incorporated, about 3 minutes. Stir in black beans, corn, chopped green chiles, and sour cream. Remove from heat and fold in chicken. &lt;img alt="A pot containing a casserole with shredded chicken and mixed ingredients stirred with a spoon" class="img--noscript mntl-image mntl-image universal-image__image" height="3000" sizes="750px" src="img/a16e0abb50d470b563f946c18b02aa87.webp" srcset="img/ecf6e63b8a3b30bbf195f545c9ef68bc.webp 750w" width="4000"&gt; Garnish with tortilla strips, cilantro, scallions, and pickled red onion. &lt;img alt="Dish of casserole garnished with sliced vegetables served on a plate with a fork" class="img--noscript mntl-image mntl-image universal-image__image" height="3000" sizes="750px" src="img/923c75c5843cbdea94de625a4225f977.webp" srcset="img/c7c35332295de8f5e3286f9137be1605.webp 750w" width="4000"&gt; * Percent Daily Values are based on a 2,000 calorie diet. Your daily values may be higher or lower depending on your calorie needs. ** Nutrient information is not available for all ingredients. Amount is based on available nutrient data. (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient. If you are following a medically restrictive diet, please consult your doctor or registered dietitian before preparing this recipe for personal consumption. Ask the Community (5) Asked by K C Chef Can black beans and corn left out of can we substitute other items I don't know why you couldn't. Just sub with same amount of beans you like (pinto, kidney, garbanzo - even combo) By JollyPizza3277 My answer 0/500 characters Asked by sharonpaterson2000 Looks like this could be even more streamlined by cooking it in a cast iron skillet and baking it in the same pan. Or is it too full by the time you add the chicken and cheese to bake in the skillet? Depends on how deep your pan is but shouldn't be an issue. By SilverWheat5153 Thank you! I’ll try it this weekend By sharonpaterson2000 I cooked it in my large, deep frying pan. It’s oven-safe so I didn’t bother transferring to a baking dish. It turned out perfectly. By chief cook My answer 0/500 characters Asked by Tabbie If I would like to use ground beef, how much would I use? Same as chicken, 1 pound. By DapperSpoon5406 My answer 0/500 characters Asked by JUDYKAZOOTIE Can you prepare ahead of time and refrigerate or freeze? I love this easy put together dish and I love the amount of protein in such a small serving. I'm post gastric bypass and the calories or fat don't bother me at all since I need to gain weight. This dish is perfect for me!! Extremely bland, much less spicy than I anticipated based on ingredients. If you want flavor, I’d suggest using HOT taco seasoning and salsa and chilies, and a blend of cheddar and pepperjack cheese on top. this Recipe is so Awesome that words cannot actually describe it. Please trust me when I say.."This Hot 🤠 Cowgirl Casserole recipe is completely hearty satisfying and delicious"You simply can't go wrong, man 👨! ! ! A keeper!Great flavorsEasy to followWorth the effortCrowd-pleaserFamily favorite Very great taste. Photos of Hot Cowgirl Casserole 01of 01 &lt;img alt="Dish of casserole garnished with sliced vegetables served on a plate with a fork" class="img--noscript universal-image__image" height="3000" src="img/8e87cf0b913f5bc44c8ae8c764b14286.webp" width="4000"&gt;
